This class is a survey of the civilization of China from prehistoric times to the present.&#8232;
&#8232;Students found this class to be an excellent introduction to Chinese civilization. There were some complaints that the pace of the course prevented many topics from being explored in depth, but most reviews were positive and found lectures to be very interesting. One student advised that lecture attendance is important because the class provides “so much more depth and meaning to the material covered by readings.”&#8232;
Students enjoyed Professor Goldin and felt he was “an animated lecturer who made the material relevant, interesting, and often entertaining.” Many explained that Professor Goldin is a true storyteller who “balances a passion for the subject matter with sufficient anecdotes to keep most students interested.” &#8232;
This course fulfills the History and Tradition Sector requirement and has no prerequisites. Students highly recommended the class to major students and those with an interest in Asian culture. Most did not find the course to be overly difficult.
